/**
 * @mainpage AnalysisG Documentation
 *
 * @section intro Introduction
 *
 * AnalysisG is a Graph Neural Network Analysis Framework for High Energy Physics.
 * It provides tools for building and training graph neural networks on particle
 * physics collision data stored in ROOT files.
 *
 * @section structure Project Structure
 *
 * The source code is organized into the following modules under `src/AnalysisG`:
 *
 * - **core** - Core data structures and base classes
 * - **events** - Event data model and ROOT file I/O
 * - **graphs** - Graph construction algorithms
 * - **metrics** - Performance metrics and evaluation tools
 * - **models** - GNN model implementations
 * - **modules** - High-level analysis modules
 * - **selections** - Event selection and filtering
 * - **templates** - Reusable template classes
 *
 * @section usage Usage
 *
 * See the project README and the individual module documentation for details.
 *
 * @section license License
 *
 * This project is licensed under the terms described in the LICENSE file.
 */
